- "high voter turnout" means a turnout percentage greater than 50%;
- "low ballot rejection rates" means the number of rejected ballots is less than 10% of the total ballots;
- "where the Democratic candidate won" means the candidate from the Democratic party received votes in that precinct.

- "Top candidates" refer to candidates who have the highest number of votes in each precinct;
- "Stars that shine the brightest" is a metaphorical expression for the most popular or influential candidates;
- "Drawing the most voters to the polls" refers to a high voter turnout;
- "Percentage of registered voters who cast their ballots" is the turnout percentage.

sql:
SELECT precinct_name
FROM precincts
ORDER BY precinct_name;

